 <!-- Introduction -->
 <!-- The introduction should start as shown: -->
 <purpose>
   <p>
This part of ISO 10303 specifies an application module for the representation of the visual attributes that govern the presentation of text in two-dimensional views.
   </p>
   
<!-- e2 text -->
	<p>The second edition of this part of ISO 10303 included the modifications to the first edition listed below.</p>
	<!-- ARM -->
	<p>The following ARM EXPRESS declarations have been added:</p>
		<ul>
			<li>font_select;</li>
			<li>Draughting_pre_defined_text_font;</li>
			<li>Externally_defined_text_font;</li>
			<li>Text_literal_with_extent.</li>
		</ul>
	<p>In addition, modifications have been made to the mapping specification, 
	the MIM schema and the EXPRESS-G diagrams to reflect and be consistent with the modifications of the ARM.</p>
	
<!-- 3rd edition -->
<p>   
This third edition of this part of ISO 10303 includes the modifications to the third edition listed below.
</p>
<!-- ARM -->
<p>The following ARM EXPRESS declarations have been added:</p>
	<ul>
		<li>USE FROM Basic_geometry_arm;</li>
		<li>Text_literal;</li>
		<li>Text_literal_with_delineation;</li>
		<li>Text_literal_with_associated_curves;</li>
		<li>Text_literal_with_blanking_box;</li>
		<li>ta_detailed_geometric_model_element_subtypes.</li>
	</ul>

<p>
	The following ARM EXPRESS data types have been added:
</p>
	<ul>
		<li>text_alignment;</li>
		<li>text_path;</li>
		<li>text_delineation.</li>
	</ul>


<p>The following ARM EXPRESS declarations have been removed:</p>
	<ul>
		<li>USE FROM Elemental_geometric_shape_arm;</li>
		<li>Presentable_text_item;</li>
		<li>Text_style.</li>
	</ul>

<p>The following ARM EXPRESS declarations have been modified:</p>
	<ul>
		<li>Text_literal_with_extent.</li>
	</ul>

<p>
	The following ARM EXPRESS data types have been modified:
</p>
	<ul>
		<li>composite_text_element_select.</li>
	</ul>

<p>In addition, modifications have been made to the mapping specification, 
	the MIM schema and the EXPRESS-G diagrams to reflect and be consistent with the modifications of the ARM.</p>
 </purpose>

